      "rawMarkdown": "## 123. Conventional\n\n**Pronunciation:** kən-VEN-shə-nəl\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Following accepted rules, customs, or standard ways.\n**Bangla meaning:** প্রচলিত, প্রথাগত, সাধারণ নিয়মমাফিক\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n*Conventional* comes from Latin *convenire*, meaning “to come together” or “to agree.” A convention is something people agree to follow.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nSomething **conventional** is normal, standard, traditional, or widely accepted.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Convention = social agreement** → conventional = what society agrees is normal.\n\n**GRE synonyms:** traditional, customary, orthodox, standard, established\n**Basic synonyms:** usual, normal, common, regular\n**Antonyms:** unconventional, original, unusual, radical, innovative\n\n**Common usage:** conventional wisdom, conventional medicine, conventional method, conventional style, conventional morality\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Conventional ≠ Convenient**\nConventional = traditional/standard.\nConvenient = easy or suitable.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. They followed a **conventional** wedding style.\n2. His clothes were simple and **conventional**.\n3. The teacher used a **conventional** method.\n4. Many patients first try **conventional** medicine before alternative treatment.\n5. The architect rejected **conventional** designs and proposed a radical structure.\n6. The company relied on **conventional** advertising rather than digital campaigns.\n7. In academic writing, **conventional** arguments often need fresh evidence.\n8. The study challenged **conventional** assumptions about economic growth.\n9. The researcher used **conventional** statistical tools before applying machine learning.\n10. GRE-style: Although the theory appeared **conventional**, its implications were surprisingly disruptive.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The village followed **traditional** customs.\n2. The lawyer used a **standard** contract.\n3. The ceremony followed **customary** rules.\n4. His beliefs were deeply **orthodox**.\n5. The scientist questioned the **established** model.\n6. The school preferred **regular** classroom instruction.\n7. The committee accepted the **usual** procedure.\n8. The company used **mainstream** marketing strategies.\n9. The report reflected **accepted** practice.\n10. The priest defended **orthodox** doctrine.\n11. The professor criticized **standardized** thinking.\n12. The policy followed **normal** administrative procedure.\n13. The court relied on **precedent-based** reasoning.\n14. The essay repeated **commonplace** views.\n15. The engineer selected a **proven** design method.\n\n**Common mistake:**\nDo not confuse **conventional** with **boring** every time. Something conventional may be ordinary, but not always bad.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Conventional = accepted standard = প্রচলিত**\n\n---",
