      "rawMarkdown": "## 126. Discernible\n\n**Pronunciation:** dih-SUR-nuh-bəl\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Able to be seen, noticed, or understood.\n**Bangla meaning:** দৃশ্যমান, বোঝা যায় এমন, শনাক্তযোগ্য\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n*Discernible* comes from Latin *discernere*, meaning “to separate, distinguish, perceive.” If something is discernible, your mind can separate it from the background.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nIf a change is **discernible**, you can notice it.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Discern = detect** → discernible = detectable.\n\n**GRE synonyms:** detectable, noticeable, observable, perceptible, apparent\n**Basic synonyms:** visible, clear, seen, noticeable\n**Antonyms:** invisible, hidden, indistinct, imperceptible, obscure\n\n**Common usage:** discernible change, discernible pattern, discernible difference, barely discernible\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Discernible ≠ Discerning**\nDiscernible = able to be noticed.\nDiscerning = having good judgment.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. There was a **discernible** smell of smoke.\n2. The difference was barely **discernible**.\n3. A **discernible** pattern appeared in the data.\n4. The medicine produced a **discernible** improvement after two weeks.\n5. The speaker’s nervousness was **discernible** in his voice.\n6. The policy had no **discernible** effect on unemployment.\n7. In research, a **discernible** correlation does not always prove causation.\n8. The satellite image showed a **discernible** change in coastline shape.\n9. The essay lacked a **discernible** thesis, making its argument difficult to follow.\n10. GRE-style: Although the reform was praised, its benefits were scarcely **discernible** in the poorest districts.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. A **detectable** rise in temperature worried the engineers.\n2. The error was **noticeable** even to beginners.\n3. The trend became **observable** after several trials.\n4. The difference was **perceptible** only under magnification.\n5. His frustration was **apparent**.\n6. The pattern was **visible** in the graph.\n7. The signal was **measurable** but weak.\n8. The damage was **evident** after inspection.\n9. The shift in tone was **clear**.\n10. The symptoms were **identifiable** by trained doctors.\n11. The improvement was **marked** after the intervention.\n12. The bias was **manifest** in the report.\n13. The contrast was **plain** to observers.\n14. The change was **recognizable** across all samples.\n15. The effect became **salient** in the final analysis.\n\n**Common mistake:**\nDo not use **discernible** when nothing can be noticed. Say “not discernible” or “barely discernible.”\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Discernible = noticeable = বোঝা যায় এমন**\n\n---",
