      "rawMarkdown": "## 130. Fanciful\n\n**Pronunciation:** FAN-sih-fəl\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Imaginative but unrealistic.\n**Bangla meaning:** অলীক, কল্পনাপ্রসূত, বাস্তবতাবর্জিত\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n*Fanciful* comes from “fancy,” meaning imagination or mental image. It suggests something created by imagination rather than reality.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nA **fanciful** idea may be creative, but it is usually unrealistic.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Fancy full of imagination = fanciful.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** imaginative, whimsical, unrealistic, fantastic, visionary\n**Basic synonyms:** dreamy, unreal, imaginary, made-up\n**Antonyms:** realistic, practical, factual, sober, grounded\n\n**Common usage:** fanciful story, fanciful idea, fanciful theory, fanciful design\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Fanciful ≠ Fancy**\nFancy can mean stylish or expensive.\nFanciful means imaginative but often unrealistic.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The child told a **fanciful** story.\n2. His plan sounded **fanciful**.\n3. The painting had **fanciful** creatures.\n4. The proposal was too **fanciful** to attract serious investors.\n5. The author mixed historical facts with **fanciful** inventions.\n6. The engineer rejected the **fanciful** design as structurally impossible.\n7. In policy debates, **fanciful** promises often ignore financial constraints.\n8. The theory was criticized as **fanciful** because no evidence supported it.\n9. The startup’s **fanciful** projections assumed unlimited customer growth.\n10. GRE-style: The reformer’s vision was inspiring, but its reliance on voluntary global cooperation made it seem **fanciful**.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The child’s story was highly **imaginative**.\n2. The artist painted a **whimsical** garden.\n3. The plan was **unrealistic**.\n4. The novel contained **fantastic** creatures.\n5. His dream of instant peace seemed **visionary** but impractical.\n6. The idea was **illusory**.\n7. The proposal was **dreamlike** rather than practical.\n8. The myth was **imaginary**.\n9. The design looked **fantastical**.\n10. The economist dismissed the forecast as **speculative**.\n11. The rumor was **baseless**.\n12. The argument rested on **fictional** assumptions.\n13. The project seemed **quixotic**.\n14. The explanation was **far-fetched**.\n15. The story’s **inventive** details delighted readers.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Fanciful** may be positive in art but negative in serious planning or academic argument.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Fanciful = imaginative but unrealistic = কল্পনাপ্রসূত**\n\n---",
