      "rawMarkdown": "## 132. Heterogeneous\n\n**Pronunciation:** het-uh-roh-JEE-nee-əs\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Made up of different kinds or parts.\n**Bangla meaning:** বিচিত্র, ভিন্নধর্মী, নানা উপাদানে গঠিত\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n*Heterogeneous* comes from Greek *heteros* = different + *genos* = kind/type. So it literally means “different kinds.”\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nA **heterogeneous** group or mixture contains many different types of people, things, or elements.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Hetero = different** → heterogeneous = different types together.\n\n**GRE synonyms:** diverse, varied, mixed, disparate, assorted\n**Basic synonyms:** different, many types, not uniform\n**Antonyms:** homogeneous, uniform, similar, identical, consistent\n\n**Common usage:** heterogeneous population, heterogeneous sample, heterogeneous mixture, heterogeneous data\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Heterogeneous ≠ Homogeneous**\nHeterogeneous = mixed/different.\nHomogeneous = same/uniform.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The class was **heterogeneous**.\n2. The city has a **heterogeneous** population.\n3. Soil is a **heterogeneous** mixture.\n4. The study used a **heterogeneous** sample of participants.\n5. The team was **heterogeneous**, including engineers, economists, and designers.\n6. The **heterogeneous** data made statistical analysis difficult.\n7. In medicine, patients with **heterogeneous** symptoms may require different treatments.\n8. The country’s **heterogeneous** society includes many languages and cultures.\n9. The researcher avoided broad conclusions because the dataset was too **heterogeneous**.\n10. GRE-style: The coalition’s strength came from its **heterogeneous** membership, but that diversity also made consensus difficult.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The neighborhood was culturally **diverse**.\n2. The results were **varied**.\n3. The committee included a **mixed** group of experts.\n4. The collection was **assorted**.\n5. The arguments were **disparate**.\n6. The population was **multifarious**.\n7. The evidence came from **different** sources.\n8. The museum displayed **eclectic** art.\n9. The team had a **diversified** skill set.\n10. The sample was **nonuniform**.\n11. The classroom contained **variegated** backgrounds.\n12. The coalition was **pluralistic**.\n13. The report combined **miscellaneous** observations.\n14. The species were **distinct**.\n15. The group was **composite**, not singular.\n\n**Common mistake:**\nDo not say “heterogeneous same group.” That is contradictory. Heterogeneous means mixed.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Heterogeneous = different kinds together = বিচিত্র**\n\n---",
