      "rawMarkdown": "## 135. Invasive\n\n**Pronunciation:** in-VAY-siv\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Spreading harmfully or entering where it is not wanted.\n**Bangla meaning:** অনধিকার প্রবেশকারী, আক্রমণাত্মকভাবে ছড়িয়ে পড়া, ক্ষতিকরভাবে প্রবেশকারী\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n*Invasive* comes from Latin *invadere*, meaning “to go into, attack, enter forcefully.” So invasive means entering or spreading in an unwanted way.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nSomething **invasive** enters a place, body, system, or environment and causes harm or discomfort.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Invasive = invades.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** intrusive, encroaching, spreading harmfully, aggressive, penetrating\n**Basic synonyms:** unwanted, entering, harmful, spreading\n**Antonyms:** noninvasive, harmless, contained, respectful, restrained\n\n**Common usage:** invasive species, invasive surgery, invasive questions, invasive technology\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Invasive ≠ Evasive**\nInvasive = entering/spreading harmfully.\nEvasive = avoiding direct answers.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The plant is **invasive**.\n2. The doctor suggested a less **invasive** test.\n3. His questions felt **invasive**.\n4. **Invasive** species can destroy local ecosystems.\n5. The app collected data in an **invasive** way.\n6. The surgery was effective but highly **invasive**.\n7. In environmental science, **invasive** organisms threaten biodiversity.\n8. The policy was criticized as **invasive** because it expanded surveillance.\n9. The researcher avoided **invasive** methods when studying vulnerable communities.\n10. GRE-style: The technology promised convenience, but critics warned that its **invasive** monitoring could erode privacy.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The reporter asked **intrusive** questions.\n2. The weeds were **encroaching** on farmland.\n3. The disease became **aggressive**.\n4. The needle test was **penetrating** but necessary.\n5. The policy felt **overreaching**.\n6. The security measures were **interfering** with daily life.\n7. The company used **obtrusive** advertising.\n8. The vines **spread** across the wall.\n9. The surveillance was **intrusive**.\n10. The species was **non-native** and destructive.\n11. The tumor showed **infiltrative** growth.\n12. The law was criticized as **meddlesome**.\n13. The software’s permissions seemed **excessive**.\n14. The army’s **incursion** destabilized the region.\n15. The new rules **encroached** on personal freedom.\n\n**Common mistake:**\nDo not confuse **invasive** with **evasive**.\nInvasive enters too much. Evasive avoids answering.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Invasive = unwanted harmful entry/spread = অনধিকার প্রবেশকারী**\n\n---\n\n# Compact Summary Table — Day 5 Part 1\n\n| No. | Word          | Core Meaning                 | Bangla             | Strong Synonyms         | Opposite       |\n| --: | ------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------- | -------------- |\n| 121 | Aloof         | emotionally distant          | উদাসীন, বিচ্ছিন্ন  | detached, reserved      | friendly       |\n| 122 | Clangor       | loud harsh noise             | কোলাহল             | clamor, din             | silence        |\n| 123 | Conventional  | standard/traditional         | প্রচলিত            | customary, orthodox     | unconventional |\n| 124 | Debunk        | prove false                  | ভুল প্রমাণ করা     | refute, disprove        | confirm        |\n| 125 | Diminutive    | very small                   | ক্ষুদ্র            | tiny, miniature         | huge           |\n| 126 | Discernible   | noticeable                   | বোঝা যায় এমন       | detectable, perceptible | hidden         |\n| 127 | Enigmatic     | mysterious                   | রহস্যময়            | cryptic, inscrutable    | clear          |\n| 128 | Estranged     | no longer close              | বিচ্ছিন্ন          | alienated, separated    | reconciled     |\n| 129 | Extravagant   | excessive/wasteful           | অমিতব্যয়ী          | lavish, prodigal        | frugal         |\n| 130 | Fanciful      | imaginative but unrealistic  | কল্পনাপ্রসূত       | whimsical, unrealistic  | realistic      |\n| 131 | Frivolous     | not serious                  | তুচ্ছ              | trivial, petty          | serious        |\n| 132 | Heterogeneous | mixed/different              | বিচিত্র            | diverse, varied         | homogeneous    |\n| 133 | Imperious     | arrogantly commanding        | দাম্ভিক            | domineering, haughty    | humble         |\n| 134 | Impertinent   | rude/disrespectful           | বেয়াদব             | insolent, impudent      | respectful     |\n| 135 | Invasive      | entering/spreading harmfully | অনধিকার প্রবেশকারী | intrusive, encroaching  | noninvasive    |\n\n---",
