      "rawMarkdown": "## 138. Lax\n\n**Pronunciation:** LAKS\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Not strict, careful, or attentive enough.\n**Bangla meaning:** শিথিল, ঢিলেঢালা, অসতর্ক, অমনোযোগী\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Lax** comes from Latin *laxus*, meaning “loose.” So the original idea is something not tight or not strict.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nA **lax** rule, teacher, guard, or system is too loose and careless.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Lax = loose** → rules are not tight.\n\n**GRE synonyms:** careless, negligent, slack, remiss, inattentive\n**Basic synonyms:** loose, weak, careless, not strict\n**Antonyms:** strict, careful, rigorous, vigilant, attentive\n\n**Common usage:** lax security, lax discipline, lax standards, lax enforcement\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Lax ≠ Relax**\nRelax = rest.\nLax = careless or not strict.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The school had **lax** rules.\n2. The guard was **lax** at the gate.\n3. **Lax** security caused the theft.\n4. The factory’s **lax** safety standards led to accidents.\n5. The teacher was criticized for being too **lax** with deadlines.\n6. The company suffered because of **lax** financial oversight.\n7. In laboratory work, **lax** procedures can ruin an experiment.\n8. The audit revealed **lax** record-keeping across several departments.\n9. The court blamed the accident partly on **lax** regulatory enforcement.\n10. GRE-style: The scandal exposed not a single mistake but a culture of **lax** supervision.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The driver was **careless** in heavy traffic.\n2. The manager was **negligent** about safety reports.\n3. The team’s **slack** discipline weakened performance.\n4. The accountant was **remiss** in checking invoices.\n5. The guard was **inattentive** during duty.\n6. The policy was **loose** and poorly enforced.\n7. The professor criticized the **casual** handling of evidence.\n8. The system was **permissive** to a dangerous degree.\n9. The agency’s **lenient** enforcement angered citizens.\n10. The editor rejected the **careless** manuscript.\n11. The supervisor showed **poor** oversight.\n12. The report described **weak** monitoring.\n13. The investigation found **sloppy** documentation.\n14. The hospital improved after ending **negligent** practices.\n15. The rule was too **relaxed** to prevent abuse.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Lax** is usually negative. It means too loose, not properly careful.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Lax = careless / not strict = শিথিল**\n\n---",
