      "rawMarkdown": "## 140. Panache\n\n**Pronunciation:** puh-NASH\n**Part of speech:** Noun\n**Core meaning:** Stylish confidence; impressive flair.\n**Bangla meaning:** আড়ম্বরপূর্ণ ভঙ্গি, সাহসী স্টাইল, আত্মবিশ্বাসী চমক\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Panache** originally referred to a plume of feathers on a helmet, a visible sign of style and bravery. Later it came to mean confident elegance.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nIf someone does something with **panache**, they do it with style, confidence, and flair.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Panache = performance + style.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** flair, style, flamboyance, elegance, verve\n**Basic synonyms:** confidence, charm, bold style\n**Antonyms:** dullness, awkwardness, plainness, timidity, clumsiness\n\n**Common usage:** with panache, perform with panache, carry oneself with panache, artistic panache\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Panache ≠ Panic**\nPanache = stylish confidence.\nPanic = sudden fear.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. She danced with **panache**.\n2. The actor entered the stage with **panache**.\n3. He solved the problem with surprising **panache**.\n4. The chef presented a simple dish with great **panache**.\n5. The speaker handled difficult questions with **panache**.\n6. The designer added **panache** to an otherwise ordinary building.\n7. In leadership, technical skill matters, but **panache** can inspire confidence.\n8. The novelist writes historical scenes with both accuracy and **panache**.\n9. The athlete’s victory celebration showed confidence without arrogance, full of **panache**.\n10. GRE-style: The proposal was not merely competent; it was delivered with such **panache** that even skeptics applauded.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The dancer performed with **flair**.\n2. The musician played with effortless **style**.\n3. His speech had dramatic **flamboyance**.\n4. The actress moved with **elegance**.\n5. The young leader spoke with **verve**.\n6. The chef added artistic **brio** to the meal.\n7. The painter’s work displayed **dash**.\n8. The professor explained the theory with intellectual **flair**.\n9. The host managed the event with **grace**.\n10. The singer performed with **confidence**.\n11. The essay showed unusual **vivacity**.\n12. The director handled the scene with cinematic **style**.\n13. The athlete competed with remarkable **elan**.\n14. The comedian delivered the joke with perfect **timing**.\n15. The designer’s collection showed visual **flamboyance**.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Panache** is usually positive. It means stylish confidence, not arrogance.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Panache = stylish confidence = আত্মবিশ্বাসী স্টাইল**\n\n---",
