      "rawMarkdown": "## 143. Remedial\n\n**Pronunciation:** rih-MEE-dee-əl\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Intended to correct, improve, or fix a problem.\n**Bangla meaning:** প্রতিকারমূলক, সংশোধনমূলক, ঘাটতি পূরণের জন্য\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Remedial** comes from **remedy**, meaning cure or solution. So remedial action is action that fixes a weakness or problem.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nA **remedial** class, course, or measure helps correct a problem or fill a gap.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Remedial = remedy-based.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** corrective, restorative, rectifying, reparative, therapeutic\n**Basic synonyms:** fixing, improving, helpful, corrective\n**Antonyms:** harmful, damaging, worsening, punitive, destructive\n\n**Common usage:** remedial class, remedial action, remedial education, remedial measure\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Remedial ≠ Immediate**\nRemedial = corrective.\nImmediate = happening now.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. He took a **remedial** math class.\n2. The school offered **remedial** English lessons.\n3. The doctor suggested **remedial** exercise.\n4. The company introduced **remedial** training after the accident.\n5. The report recommended **remedial** measures to fix water pollution.\n6. The student needed **remedial** instruction before joining the advanced course.\n7. In engineering, **remedial** maintenance can prevent structural failure.\n8. The government adopted **remedial** policies to reduce educational inequality.\n9. The audit identified errors and proposed **remedial** steps.\n10. GRE-style: The reform was not punitive but **remedial**, designed to correct systemic weaknesses.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The teacher gave **corrective** feedback.\n2. The therapy had a **restorative** effect.\n3. The policy was **rectifying** past injustice.\n4. The repair was **reparative**.\n5. The treatment was **therapeutic**.\n6. The engineer proposed **repairing** the damaged beam.\n7. The law aimed at **redressing** inequality.\n8. The coach offered **instructional** support.\n9. The program was **compensatory**.\n10. The class helped **improve** weak skills.\n11. The committee recommended **corrective** action.\n12. The medication was **curative** in mild cases.\n13. The training was **rehabilitative**.\n14. The policy was designed to **remedy** past neglect.\n15. The intervention was **ameliorative**, not punitive.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Remedial** is often used for education, law, medicine, and policy. It means fixing a deficiency.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Remedial = corrective / fixing = প্রতিকারমূলক**\n\n---",
