      "rawMarkdown": "## 144. Restive\n\n**Pronunciation:** RES-tiv\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Restless, uneasy, impatient, or difficult to control.\n**Bangla meaning:** অস্থির, অশান্ত, অস্থিরচিত্ত, নিয়ন্ত্রণে কঠিন\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Restive** originally described a horse that refused to move forward and became difficult to control. Now it means restless or impatient.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nA **restive** crowd, animal, or group is uneasy and may become difficult to manage.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Restive sounds like restless** → unable to stay calm.\n\n**GRE synonyms:** restless, uneasy, agitated, impatient, unruly\n**Basic synonyms:** nervous, unsettled, fidgety, disturbed\n**Antonyms:** calm, peaceful, patient, composed, settled\n\n**Common usage:** restive crowd, restive students, restive horse, restive population\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Restive ≠ Restful**\nRestive = restless/uneasy.\nRestful = peaceful and relaxing.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The children became **restive**.\n2. The crowd grew **restive** after the delay.\n3. The horse was **restive** before the race.\n4. The students became **restive** during the long lecture.\n5. The population grew **restive** under strict economic controls.\n6. The audience became **restive** when the speaker avoided the main issue.\n7. In politics, a **restive** public can force rapid policy change.\n8. The company’s employees became **restive** after months without salary increases.\n9. The soldiers were **restive** after weeks of unclear orders.\n10. GRE-style: The leader’s vague promises failed to calm a **restive** electorate demanding immediate reform.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The crowd was **restless**.\n2. The patient seemed **uneasy**.\n3. The protesters became **agitated**.\n4. The passengers were **impatient**.\n5. The classroom grew **unruly**.\n6. The horse was **fidgety**.\n7. The workers were **discontented**.\n8. The citizens became **rebellious**.\n9. The child looked **nervous**.\n10. The meeting turned **turbulent**.\n11. The market remained **unsettled**.\n12. The crowd was **edgy** before the announcement.\n13. The audience became **irritable**.\n14. The village was **disturbed** by the rumor.\n15. The group showed **resistance** to authority.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Restive** does not mean restful. It means the opposite: uneasy, restless, impatient.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Restive = restless and uneasy = অস্থির**\n\n---",
