      "rawMarkdown": "## 145. Sporadic\n\n**Pronunciation:** spuh-RAD-ik\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Happening occasionally, irregularly, or at intervals.\n**Bangla meaning:** অনিয়মিত, ছিটেফোঁটা, মাঝে মাঝে ঘটে এমন\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Sporadic** comes from Greek *sporadikos*, meaning “scattered.” So sporadic events are scattered across time or place.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nIf something is **sporadic**, it does not happen continuously. It happens now and then.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Sporadic = scattered spots of activity.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** occasional, infrequent, irregular, intermittent, scattered\n**Basic synonyms:** now and then, sometimes, not regular\n**Antonyms:** regular, constant, continuous, frequent, steady\n\n**Common usage:** sporadic rain, sporadic violence, sporadic attendance, sporadic symptoms\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Sporadic ≠ Spontaneous**\nSporadic = irregular.\nSpontaneous = unplanned.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. There was **sporadic** rain all day.\n2. His attendance was **sporadic**.\n3. We heard **sporadic** gunfire.\n4. The internet connection was **sporadic** during the storm.\n5. The patient reported **sporadic** pain in the knee.\n6. The company made only **sporadic** attempts to improve safety.\n7. In research, **sporadic** data collection can weaken reliability.\n8. The protest continued with **sporadic** clashes between police and demonstrators.\n9. The reform produced **sporadic** improvements but no systematic change.\n10. GRE-style: Although the policy generated **sporadic** success stories, it failed to produce consistent national progress.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The attacks were **occasional**.\n2. The rainfall was **infrequent**.\n3. The schedule was **irregular**.\n4. The noise was **intermittent**.\n5. The reports were **scattered**.\n6. The disease appeared in **isolated** cases.\n7. The updates were **periodic** but unpredictable.\n8. The signal was **patchy**.\n9. The symptoms were **episodic**.\n10. The meetings were **rare**.\n11. The evidence was **fragmentary**.\n12. The support was **inconsistent**.\n13. The fires occurred **now and then**.\n14. The violence was **localized**.\n15. The campaign produced **uneven** results.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Sporadic** does not mean rare only. It means irregular and scattered.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Sporadic = irregular / occasional = অনিয়মিত**\n\n---",
