      "rawMarkdown": "## 147. Undermine\n\n**Pronunciation:** un-dər-MYN\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To weaken gradually or secretly.\n**Bangla meaning:** দুর্বল করা, ভিত নষ্ট করা, ক্ষতিসাধন করা\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Undermine** literally means to dig under something, weakening its foundation. Figuratively, it means to weaken power, trust, confidence, or stability.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nTo **undermine** something is to damage it from below or from within.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Under + mine** → dig under the foundation → weaken.\n\n**GRE synonyms:** weaken, sabotage, subvert, erode, impair\n**Basic synonyms:** damage, hurt, reduce strength, weaken slowly\n**Antonyms:** strengthen, support, reinforce, fortify, stabilize\n\n**Common usage:** undermine confidence, undermine authority, undermine democracy, undermine trust\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Undermine ≠ Underline**\nUndermine = weaken.\nUnderline = draw a line under text.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. Lies can **undermine** trust.\n2. The scandal **undermined** his reputation.\n3. Poor sleep can **undermine** health.\n4. The manager’s criticism **undermined** employee confidence.\n5. Corruption can **undermine** public institutions.\n6. The witness’s contradiction **undermined** the lawyer’s argument.\n7. In engineering, small cracks can **undermine** structural integrity.\n8. The report **undermined** the government’s claim of economic success.\n9. Repeated delays **undermined** public faith in the project.\n10. GRE-style: The theory seemed elegant, but new experimental evidence **undermined** its central assumption.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The leak **weakened** the administration.\n2. The spy tried to **sabotage** the mission.\n3. The rebels sought to **subvert** the regime.\n4. Years of neglect **eroded** public trust.\n5. The illness **impaired** his concentration.\n6. The scandal **damaged** her credibility.\n7. The rumor **compromised** the investigation.\n8. The decision **destabilized** the coalition.\n9. The false data **invalidated** the conclusion.\n10. The criticism **diminished** his authority.\n11. The policy **weakened** worker protections.\n12. The mistake **jeopardized** the project.\n13. The delay **hampered** progress.\n14. The evidence **challenged** the assumption.\n15. The dispute **fractured** team unity.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Undermine** often means indirect weakening, not open attack.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Undermine = weaken from below/within = ভিত দুর্বল করা**\n\n---",
