      "rawMarkdown": "## 148. Utterly\n\n**Pronunciation:** UT-er-lee\n**Part of speech:** Adverb\n**Core meaning:** Completely; absolutely.\n**Bangla meaning:** সম্পূর্ণভাবে, একেবারে, পুরোপুরি\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Utterly** comes from *utter*, meaning complete or total in older usage. It intensifies an adjective or verb.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\n**Utterly** means totally or completely, often with strong feeling.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Utterly = ultimate level completely.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** completely, absolutely, totally, entirely, wholly\n**Basic synonyms:** fully, very, quite, altogether\n**Antonyms:** partly, slightly, somewhat, incompletely, partially\n\n**Common usage:** utterly wrong, utterly impossible, utterly convinced, utterly destroyed\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Utterly ≠ Utter**\nUtter = speak or complete depending on use.\nUtterly = completely.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. I was **utterly** tired.\n2. The answer was **utterly** wrong.\n3. She was **utterly** shocked.\n4. The plan was **utterly** unrealistic.\n5. The village was **utterly** destroyed by the storm.\n6. The evidence made his defense **utterly** unconvincing.\n7. In academic writing, an **utterly** unsupported claim weakens the whole argument.\n8. The experiment failed because the assumptions were **utterly** flawed.\n9. The critic found the explanation **utterly** inadequate.\n10. GRE-style: The official’s denial seemed **utterly** implausible once the documents were released.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The claim was **completely** false.\n2. She was **absolutely** certain.\n3. The building was **totally** destroyed.\n4. The argument was **entirely** unpersuasive.\n5. The project was **wholly** unsuccessful.\n6. He was **fully** aware of the risk.\n7. The theory was **thoroughly** discredited.\n8. The room was **perfectly** silent.\n9. The idea was **altogether** unrealistic.\n10. The evidence was **decisively** against him.\n11. The reform was **fundamentally** flawed.\n12. The interpretation was **plainly** wrong.\n13. The result was **unambiguously** negative.\n14. The policy was **entirely** ineffective.\n15. The conclusion was **absolutely** clear.\n\n**Common mistake:**\n**Utterly** is strong. Do not overuse it for small things.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Utterly = completely = সম্পূর্ণভাবে**\n\n---",
