      "rawMarkdown": "## 149. Weary\n\n**Pronunciation:** WEER-ee\n**Part of speech:** Adjective / Verb\n**Core meaning:** Very tired, especially after effort, worry, or long experience.\n**Bangla meaning:** ক্লান্ত, অবসন্ন, পরিশ্রান্ত\n\n**Root story / etymology idea:**\n**Weary** comes from old Germanic roots meaning tired or exhausted. It can describe physical tiredness or emotional exhaustion.\n\n**Simple explanation:**\nA **weary** person is tired in body, mind, or spirit.\n\n**Memory hook:**\n**Weary = worn out.**\n\n**GRE synonyms:** tired, exhausted, fatigued, drained, worn out\n**Basic synonyms:** sleepy, weak, tired, bored of something\n**Antonyms:** energetic, refreshed, vigorous, rested, lively\n\n**Common usage:** weary traveler, weary worker, grow weary of excuses, weary voice\n\n**Confusing word:**\n**Weary ≠ Wary**\nWeary = tired.\nWary = cautious.\n\n### Examples — 10\n\n1. The travelers were **weary**.\n2. I felt **weary** after studying all night.\n3. Her voice sounded **weary**.\n4. The workers grew **weary** after hours of lifting heavy boxes.\n5. Citizens became **weary** of empty political promises.\n6. The doctor looked **weary** after a long emergency shift.\n7. In literature, a **weary** narrator may reveal emotional exhaustion.\n8. The public grew **weary** of repeated scandals.\n9. The researcher was **weary** but continued checking the data.\n10. GRE-style: After years of inconclusive debate, even the most passionate scholars became **weary** of the controversy.\n\n### GRE Synonym Examples — 15\n\n1. The hikers were **tired**.\n2. The nurse felt **exhausted**.\n3. The athlete was **fatigued** after training.\n4. The long argument left him emotionally **drained**.\n5. The old soldier looked **worn out**.\n6. The students were **spent** after the exam.\n7. The worker was **depleted** of energy.\n8. The team felt **enervated** by the heat.\n9. The endless routine made her **jaded**.\n10. The villagers were **worn** by years of conflict.\n11. The professor sounded **tired** of repeating the point.\n12. The journey left them **exhausted**.\n13. The public became **sick of** corruption.\n14. The candidate appeared **fatigued** during the final debate.\n15. The long negotiation left both sides **drained**.\n\n**Common mistake:**\nDo not confuse **weary** with **wary**.\nWeary = tired.\nWary = careful.\n\n**Final memory:**\n**Weary = tired / worn out = ক্লান্ত**\n\n---",
